before

public boolean before(UTime t1)

Compares this timestamp with the input, returning true if the input time is before this timestamp.

Note that if this timestamp represents an interval, this function will only return true if the input time occurs before both the start and end times of this interval. To compare only with the start time, use UTime#beforeStart(long) instead.

Parameters:
t1 - Timestamp to compare
Returns:

before

public boolean before(long msec)

Compares this timestamp with the input, returning true if the input time is before this timestamp.

Note that if this timestamp represents an interval, this function will only return true if the input time occurs before both the start and end times of this interval. To compare only with the start time, use UTime#beforeStart(long) instead.

Parameters:
msec - Time in msec to compare with
Returns:
